SIMPLE: foredeem
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foredeem
<hw>Fore*deem"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To recognize or
judge in advance; to forebode.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Udall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Laugh at your misery, as <qex>foredeeming</qex> you⟦br⟧
An idle meteor.</q> <rj><qau>J. Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foredeem</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foredeem
<hw>Fore*deem"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Foredoom</er>.]</ety> <def>To know or discover beforehand; to
foretell.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Which [maid] could guess and <qex>foredeem</qex> of things past,
present, and to come.</q> <rj><qau>Genevan Test.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foredesign</ent>⟦br⟧
